The paper discusses the relevance of bibliometric-enhanced information retrieval services for researchers in the social sciences. The services include search term, journal name, and author name recommenders, which are relevant to the fields of information retrieval (cs.IR) and digital libraries (cs.DL). The study also involves assessing the recommendations' relevance, which could fall under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of bibliometrics, which could relate to the sub-categories of cybersecurity (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
